column5: Just hours after having my Motors lower end replaced and getting her back the water the Muskie gods have smiled upon us!  On this abnormally hot day (28 degrees), a couple of friends and I got on the water as soon as we could and went to work.  The day started slow but we kept working and landed this nice 53".  She spit out the bait almost before we netted her so much thanks to Craig for an excellent netting job...  After a few pics from the flashing black box and a quick measurement, she was back in the water and on her way like nothing happened.  What a gorgeous fish!
Nice fish!  4 degrees below freezing you say? lol
beauty! and 28 Fahrenheit!,?!? I think Celsius hahaha
Hey thats Lew,s fish. LOL  Dang thats a nice fish there. Congrats.  You guys sure are hearty wearing T,s in those temps.
Very Nice Regan, she's a beaut for sure.
Awesome.   So there are nice fish in the west arm.  LOL
A beautiful specimen, Regan. Congrats. You certainly put in your time. UMMMM Regan ol' buddy, any chance you're marking the way points for our future trips?
Hey Regan, beauty fish great stuff! As Roy says hope you are marking those way points.....lol.
that is a true trophy!!!  cheers
Awesome ski congrats that is a piggy
Beauty fish, your setting your PB pretty high, looking forward of pics when you top that one
